&lt;h2 id=&quot;h-who-we-are&quot;&gt;Who we are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coefficient is a VC-backed SaaS startup based in the SF Bay Area. We are building a remote-first company with a focus on hiring the best talent regardless of location. Our culture is centered around people who are smart, driven, curious and collaborative. We are embarking on a journey to unleash the power and flexibility of spreadsheets across all of the data in company systems. The founders are serial entrepreneurs whose last startup, Shopular, was backed by Y Combinator and Sequoia and acquired by Rakuten Ebates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;h-what-we-do&quot;&gt;What we do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coefficient provides a no-code solution that enables business teams to access their company data in real-time directly from their spreadsheets and make it actionable across the organization. Whether their data lives in business applications, databases, data warehouses, or business intelligence solutions, business users can easily work with this data without IT involvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Using Coefficient, business teams can be more effective with company data that’s connected, automated and performant in the most familiar and flexible analytics product – their spreadsheet. By meeting users where they are, companies can now reduce friction between IT and business teams to drive higher efficiency and growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;h-job-description&quot;&gt;Job Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are hiring our founding Sales Development Representatives. This role is responsible for identifying, generating, and qualifying net new opportunities. You’ll be an integral part of our go-to-market team as we scale up our outbound motion. We promote from within and this role is seen as a ‘bench’ for our future AE hires. &lt;strong&gt;This is a hybrid role that will spend a few days a week in our Austin office.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;h-responsibilities&quot;&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive top of funnel for our Commercial Account Executive team by identifying and creating net new pipeline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Qualify prospects to help accelerate deal cycles&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Become an Coefficient expert and deeply understand our core personas, their pain points, and our value propositions&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and execute campaigns across email, LinkedIn, phone, and other channels by creating thoughtful messaging that articulates the value our product provides&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Grow our GTM team by constantly innovating and trying out new tactics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;h-responsibilities&quot;&gt;Qualifications&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;gt;6 months prior experience in a business development role in B2B SAAS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort with ambiguity. You’re an independent thinker who asks for help when needed, but is comfortable charting a path forward in an uncertain environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Desire to grow, learn, and develop your career in B2B sales. High conviction that tech sales is your target path, and strong drive to achieve your goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High professionalism and attention to detail. You hold yourself and your work to an extremely high standard&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coefficient is a VC-backed startup building the next generation of data software. The founders, Navneet &amp;amp; Tommy, are serial entrepreneurs whose last startup, Shopular, was backed by Y Combinator and Sequoia and acquired by Rakuten Ebates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We started by turning spreadsheets into a live, connected layer on top of company data—bringing systems like Salesforce, HubSpot, and Snowflake directly into Google Sheets and Excel. Today, thousands of teams rely on Coefficient to access real-time data without IT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now, we’re taking the next step.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Building&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coefficient is evolving into an &lt;strong&gt;agentic data intelligence platform &lt;/strong&gt;— where AI doesn’t just retrieve data, but understands it, reasons about it, and takes action.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At the core is a shared &lt;strong&gt;data world model&lt;/strong&gt;: a unified, continuously updated understanding of a company’s data, business logic, and context. This allows our autonomous agents to operate with far more context than traditional tools—unlocking a fundamentally new way to work with data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Instead of dashboards and one-off queries, we’re building AI agents that:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop context over time (memory + business rules)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explore data and surface insights proactively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute workflows and make decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate complete, high-quality outputs (reports, dashboards, spreadsheets, scripts)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All powered by the real-time, production-grade data pipelines we’ve already built.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The shift is simple:&lt;/strong&gt; from tools that show you data → to autonomous agents that &lt;strong&gt;do work with it&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for Product Engineers early in their career who operate with &lt;strong&gt;high agency, strong ownership, and deep curiosity&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a scoped, ticket-driven role. You’ll work directly with the founders to define product direction, build core systems, and ship end-to-end experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You might be a fit if you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take full ownership of problems—from idea to production&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are relentlessly curious and think from first principles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Move quickly, make decisions, and iterate without perfect specs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Care deeply about product quality, UX, and craft&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thrive in ambiguity and low-structure environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical expectations:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2–4 years of experience building production web applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;fbqlxi&quot; data-start=&quot;2173&quot; data-end=&quot;2243&quot;&gt;Proficiency in modern web stacks (e.g. TypeScript, React, Next.js, or similar)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;pjaqzi&quot; data-start=&quot;2244&quot; data-end=&quot;2321&quot;&gt;Experience with backend systems and APIs (e.g. Node, Python, Flask, or similar)&lt;/li&gt;
